Name: MRS.ARCHANA RAJAN
Technique:
Volume scan of chest was done without intravenous contrast. Ultrahigh resolution scans of both 
lungs were done.
Observation:
Thin linear fibrotic bands noted in inferior lingual segment of left upper lobe and lateral 
basal segment of left lower lobe.  
Subtle subpleural basal reticular pattern noted in bilateral lung fields.  
Trachea and bifurcation are normally seen.  
No bronchial thickening or bronchiectasis is seen.  
Lung parenchyma are clear. Both hila appear normal.  
There are no air space opacities, interstitial thickening, or emphysematous changes.  
No significant mediastinal lymphnode enlargement or mass lesion is seen.  
Thoracic esophagus is grossly normal.  
No pericardial effusion. No pleural effusion is seen on either side.  
Bony thoracic cage is normal.No lytic or sclerotic lesion in visualized bones.
Impression:
 Thin linear fibrotic bands in inferior lingual segment of left upper lobe and lateral 
basal segment of left lower lobe.  Subtle subpleural basal reticular pattern noted in 
bilateral lung fields  - features suggestive of post  infective sequelae  
 No other significant abnormality seen in both lungs.
